# Dev-only TLS termination.
#
# Browsers only expose camera/microphone (getUserMedia) in a "secure context":
# HTTPS, or http://localhost. Over a plain-HTTP LAN IP (http://192.168.x.x:3000)
# the video call page can never start. This proxy puts HTTPS in front of the
# Next app so the call works across LAN devices while you keep using
# `docker compose up`.
#
# Uses a self-signed cert (certs/cert.pem) generated by scripts/gen-dev-cert.sh,
# which lists your LAN IP in its SAN so the TLS handshake works when devices
# connect by IP. (Caddy's built-in `tls internal` does NOT work for bare IP
# addresses — it aborts the handshake with ERR_SSL_PROTOCOL_ERROR.)
#
# Each device shows a ONE-TIME "not private" warning the first time — click
# through it (Advanced -> Proceed). After that the camera/mic prompt appears.
#
# Setup:  ./scripts/gen-dev-cert.sh   then   docker compose up
# Open:   https://<your-lan-ip>/   (port 443, NOT :3000) on each device.
:443 {
	tls /certs/cert.pem /certs/key.pem
	reverse_proxy app:3000
}
